race.comment: RACE TO ARMS (2) showed promise on debut then backed it up with a strong all-the-way win at Coonamble. Draws low and looks perfectly placed to go back-to-back. BRUTAL LOVE (1) has been consistent, placing in his last two including a close second at Bathurst. Doesn't need to lift much to be in the finish again. HANNAH'S BRIDGE (4) resumes after a solid debut prep and has been tuned up with two trials. Drawn ideally and should be right in the mix. GLOWING RAPIDS (6) improved last start at Forbes and has more to offer. Worth including.
